<subSubSection id="C31265792157FFFAFF721B92FEDBFD4D" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF721B92FC55FEA5" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF721B92FECAFF55" bold="true" box="[199,340,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF721B92FED3FF55" bold="true" box="[199,333,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head wider than long (1.3 times). Thorax: pronotum wider than long (3.7 times) with a yellow longitudinal median line (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE7E1BBEFDB5FF31" box="[459,555,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Meso and metapleura with punctures concentrated in spots. Metasternal process with long, digitiform, anterior arms, sometimes bearing a green line. Abdomen: posterolateral angles of the connexival segment VII, long, exceeding the angles of laterotergites and 
<quantity id="4CF09B172157FFFAFC671A06FC60FEF9" box="[978,1022,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.286" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" unit="in" value="9.0">9 in</quantity>
the female (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFB381A06FB76FEF9" box="[1165,1256,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[153,1418,576,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-159@4.[153,1434,561,1788]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of G. hamata comb.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Dr: Dorsal rim. Vf8: Valvifers 8. Vf9: Valvifer 9. Gc: Genital cup. Lt8: Laterotergites 8. Lt9: Laterotergites 9. Prc: Proctiger. Pla: Posterolateral angles. Pr: Parameres. Pyg: Pygophore. Vr: Ventral Rim. X: Segment X. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500673/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
); angle dorsally dark brown and ventrally brown. Pair of trichobothria lateral to spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF721A4FFD4BFDFD" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF721A4FFE9CFE81" bold="true" box="[199,258,330,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFEA41A4EFE12FE81" box="[273,396,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[153,1418,576,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-159@4.[153,1434,561,1788]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of G. hamata comb.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Dr: Dorsal rim. Vf8: Valvifers 8. Vf9: Valvifer 9. Gc: Genital cup. Lt8: Laterotergites 8. Lt9: Laterotergites 9. Prc: Proctiger. Pla: Posterolateral angles. Pr: Parameres. Pyg: Pygophore. Vr: Ventral Rim. X: Segment X. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500673/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 2A–C</figureCitation>
). Pygophore yellow, elongated (1.3 times longer than wide). Dorsal rim rounded, dark brown, medially slightly projected (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE6C1A6AFDAAFE6D" box="[473,564,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Superior processes of the genital cup small, reniform, medially excavated, touching dorsal rim (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE3B1A96FE74FE49" box="[398,490,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[153,1418,576,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-159@4.[153,1434,561,1788]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of G. hamata comb.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Dr: Dorsal rim. Vf8: Valvifers 8. Vf9: Valvifer 9. Gc: Genital cup. Lt8: Laterotergites 8. Lt9: Laterotergites 9. Prc: Proctiger. Pla: Posterolateral angles. Pr: Parameres. Pyg: Pygophore. Vr: Ventral Rim. X: Segment X. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500673/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Parameres with a lobe anteriorly directed long and straight and a lobe dorsally directed curved and shorter than the other. Proctiger light brown, elongated (1.6 times), wider ventrally; posterior surface laterally sloping (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE021ADEFD8FFE11" box="[439,529,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[153,1418,576,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-159@4.[153,1434,561,1788]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of G. hamata comb.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Dr: Dorsal rim. Vf8: Valvifers 8. Vf9: Valvifer 9. Gc: Genital cup. Lt8: Laterotergites 8. Lt9: Laterotergites 9. Prc: Proctiger. Pla: Posterolateral angles. Pr: Parameres. Pyg: Pygophore. Vr: Ventral Rim. X: Segment X. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500673/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim concave; expansions not projected but tumid (
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFB0D1ADEFAA6FE11" box="[1208,1336,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[153,1418,576,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-159@4.[153,1434,561,1788]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of G. hamata comb.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Dr: Dorsal rim. Vf8: Valvifers 8. Vf9: Valvifer 9. Gc: Genital cup. Lt8: Laterotergites 8. Lt9: Laterotergites 9. Prc: Proctiger. Pla: Posterolateral angles. Pr: Parameres. Pyg: Pygophore. Vr: Ventral Rim. X: Segment X. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500673/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Figs 2B–C</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface with black stripe parallel to the ventral rim.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF721927FEDBFD4D" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF721927FE80FDD9" bold="true" box="[199,286,546,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A772157FFFAFE991926FE1BFDD9" box="[300,389,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[153,1418,576,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-159@4.[153,1434,561,1788]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of G. hamata comb.n. A–C: Male genitalia. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. D: Female genital plates in ventral view. Dr: Dorsal rim. Vf8: Valvifers 8. Vf9: Valvifer 9. Gc: Genital cup. Lt8: Laterotergites 8. Lt9: Laterotergites 9. Prc: Proctiger. Pla: Posterolateral angles. Pr: Parameres. Pyg: Pygophore. Vr: Ventral Rim. X: Segment X. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500673/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 wider than long (1.1 times); slightly separated; posterior margin acuminate; dense and irregularly punctuated. Valvulae 8 partially visible between valvifers 8. Valvifer 9 wider than long (2.2 times) and setulose. Laterotergites 8 with a long distal spine as long as segment X. Laterotergites 9 flattened shorter than laterotergites 8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31265792157FFFAFF7219B6FAC9FC2E" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB736F22157FFFAFF7219B6FD36FCB9" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF7219B6FED7FD29" bold="true" box="[199,329,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B032157FFFAFEE419B6FE6DFD2A" author="Walker, F." box="[337,499,691,718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" pagination="419 - 599" refId="ref10477" refString="Walker, F. (1868) s. n. In: Catalogue of the specimens of Hemiptera-Heteroptera in the collection of the British Museum. Part III. British Museum, London, pp. 419 - 599. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9254" type="book chapter" year="1868">Walker (1868)</bibRefCitation>
described the antennae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712157FFFAFC9119B6FC07FD29" authorityName="Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Silva &amp; Fernandes" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[804,921,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFC9119B6FC07FD29" box="[804,921,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">E. hamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as being black, but they are dark brown. The description also cites four stripes on the head, the same observed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B032157FFFAFC2B19D2FB42FD16" author="Correia, A. O. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M." box="[926,1244,727,754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" pagination="541 - 565" refId="ref10259" refString="Correia, A. O. &amp; Fernandes, J. A. M. (2016) Grammedessa, a new genus of Edessinae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Pentatomidae). Zootaxa, 4107 (4), 541 - 565. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4107.4.4" type="journal article" year="2016">Correia &amp; Fernandes (2016)</bibRefCitation>
when describing 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712157FFFAFF2219FEFEA9FCF1" authorityName="Correia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,311,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFF2219FEFEA9FCF1" box="[151,311,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Grammedessa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, the two central stripes of the head are four stripes, totaling eight stripes on the head, four on each side. This species is easily distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D712157FFFAFCA6181AFC2DFCDD" authorityName="Correia &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2016" box="[787,947,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE02157FFFAFCA6181AFC2DFCDD" box="[787,947,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="216">Grammedessa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its posterolateral angles of the pronotum extremely developed, and parameres Y-shaped.
</paragraph>
